The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The Eastern Railway will run 96 Puja specials between October 3 and November 13, an official said on Monday. Thirty-four of the trains will run between Howrah and New Delhi, 10 between Howrah and Dehra Dun, 12 between Howrah and Bikaner, 10 between Sealdah and New Jalpaiguri, 10 between Howrah and New Jalpaiguri, and 20 between Howrah and Guwahati.

 Passengers on the reservation waiting list, who had booked tickets till August 20 for trips during the Pujas, will be given priority while allotting berths in the special trains. The tickets will be confirmed on a first-come-first-served basis from counters 13 and 14 at the Koilaghat reservation office on August 22 and 23.

 The Eastern Railway also announced that extra coaches would be attached to 11 pairs of regular long-distance trains between October 3 and November 21. The trains are the Howrah-New Delhi Rajdhani Express (via Gaya), Howrah-New Delhi Rajdhani Express (via Patna), Darjeeling Mail, Uttar Banga Express, Kanchan Kanya Express, Doon Express, Ananya Express, Saraighat Express, Kanchanjunga Express, Howrah-Agra Cantt. Chambal Express and the Howrah-Gwalior Chambal Express. 

 A 42-year-old teacher of a Higher Secondary school, Amitava Upadhyay, committed suicide by consuming poison at his residence in Sonarpur, on the southern fringes of the city, on Monday. Police said Upadhyay had been suffering from depression. He was taken to a local nursing home, where he died. 

 Pawan Agarwal, a trader, lost Rs 50,000 to a pickpocket while travelling in a bus. He realised the theft at Maniktala, where he got off and lodged a complaint with the local police station. 

 eputy commissioner, eastern suburban division, Vineet Goyal said an officer of Maniktala thana arrested a man, from whom Rs 10,000 was recovered. After interrogating him, raids were carried out in Barasat, from where another Rs 28,500 was recovered. 

 Two persons were killed and one was seriously injured when a car rammed into a truck parked on National Highway 6 in South Korola, under Howrah?s Domjur police station, early on Monday. One of passengers in the car died on the spot and another died on the way to Howrah State General Hospital. The driver of the car was admitted to the hospital in a critical condition. None of them could be identified. 

 The decomposed body of a 25-year-old youth was found in a goods train at Budge Budge station on Monday afternoon. Police suspect the youth was murdered a couple of days ago and the body was dumped in the train.

 Tahidur Laskar, wanted in connection with his wife?s murder, was arrested in Baruipur, on the southern fringes of the city, early on Monday. When police raided his house, Laskar allegedly fired several rounds at them from a revolver. No one was injured. Five revolvers and two cartridges were seized from the house. 

 A three-day seminar organised by the All India Railwaymen?s Federation, in collaboration with International Transport Workers? Federation, will conclude on Tuesday. Fifty participants from 16 railway zones, six production units and MTP/Calcutta are deliberating on various issues regarding welfare of railway workers.

